					"numinlets" : 1,
					"numoutlets" : 0,
					"patching_rect" : [ 21.0, 63.0, 620.0, 74.0 ],
					"text" : "Maps an input to the first inlet to a continuous sigmoid/logit function (S or sideways-S curve). The steepness of the S curve in both cases can be defined with a parameter in the second inlet.\nUnlike the simpler [sigmoid-logit] abstraction, this one provides a second parameter which defines a shift along either the x-axis or y-axis for more flexibility. However, the math is considerably more complex... if that matters to anyone."
